'''Martin Zlomislić''' (born 16 August 1998) is a Bosnian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[HNK Rijeka]] and [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

He started his professional career at [[NK Široki Brijeg|Široki Brijeg]] in 2017, at the age of 19.

==Club career==
===Široki Brijeg===
Zlomislić started playing [[Association football|football]] in [[NK Široki Brijeg|Široki Brijeg]]. He got called up to the first team in June 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/siroki-brijeg-poceo-pripreme-ekipi-se-prikljucio-novi-igrac/240130|title=Široki Brijeg počeo pripreme, ekipi se priključio novi igrač|date=7 June 2017|accessdate=7 June 2017|language=Bosnian|author=E. Čaušević|publisher=sportsport.ba}}</ref> but didn't make his professional debut for the club until 13 May 2018, which was a 3–1 home league win against [[FK Željezničar Sarajevo|Željezničar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/05/13/bosnia-herzegovina/premier-liga/nk-iroki-brijeg/fk-eljeznicar-sarajevo/2785303/|title=Široki Brijeg 3–1 Željezničar|date=13 May 2018|accessdate=13 May 2018|language=English|website=Soccerway|publisher=Perform Group}}</ref> Zlomislić didn't become a first team regular until the [[2019–20 Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina|2019–20]] season, playing in 18 of Široki's 23 games in the first part of the season.<ref name="soccerway">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/martin-zlomisli/478334/|title=M. Zlomislić: Summary|access-date=10 March 2021|language=en|website=Soccerway|publisher=Perform Group}}</ref>

He started off the [[2020–21 Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina|2020–21 Bosnian Premier League]] season with a clean sheet in a 1–0 win against [[FK Tuzla City|Tuzla City]] on 2 August 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/sport/nogomet/siroki-brijeg-na-pecari-pobijedio-tuzla-city-pogledajte-tabelu-nakon-1-kola/200802088|title=Široki Brijeg na Pecari pobijedio Tuzla City, pogledajte tabelu nakon 1. kola|date=2 August 2020|accessdate=2 August 2020|language=Bosnian|author=K.H.|publisher=Klix.ba}}</ref>

In a league game against [[FK Sloboda Tuzla|Sloboda Tuzla]] on 29 August 2020, Zlomislić earned himself a straight [[Penalty card#Red card|red card]] after fouling an opposing player.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sport1.oslobodjenje.ba/premijer-liga-bih/siroki-brijeg-oslabljen-u-duelu-sa-zeljeznicarom/198319|title=Široki Brijeg oslabljen u duelu sa Željezničarom|date=29 August 2020|access-date=29 August 2020|language=bs|publisher=Sport1.ba}}</ref>

On 31 March 2021, he terminated his contract with Široki Brijeg and left the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/martin-zlomislic-raskid-saradnje-nk-siroki-brijeg/395334|title=Martin Zlomislić raskinuo saradnju sa NK Široki Brijeg|date=31 March 2021|access-date=31 March 2021|language=bs|author=M. Šljivak|publisher=sportsport.ba}}</ref>

==International career==
Zlomislić represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-19 football team|under-19]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/toni-karacic-odabrao-reprezentativce/203175|title=Toni Karačić odabrao reprezentativce|date=11 August 2016|accessdate=11 August 2016|language=Bosnian|author=M. Šljivak|publisher=sportsport.ba}}</ref> and [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-21 football team|under-21]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/zlomislic-marinovicev-poziv-je-nagrada-i-motiv/330442|title=Zlomislić: Marinovićev poziv je nagrada i motiv|date=20 August 2019|accessdate=20 August 2019|language=Bosnian|author=A. Pašić|publisher=sportsport.ba}}</ref> level, making 1 [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for the under-19 and 2 caps for the under-21 national team respectively.<ref name="soccerway"/>

He played his first match for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|senior team]] in a [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A#Group 3|UEFA Nations League]] match against Netherlands on 19 November 2024. The match finished 1-1, as Bosnia were already relegated even before the match.

